<|startoftext|>For some reason, my husband and I fell into the wrong category.  I wanted to start a blog but was a bit annoyed by all the yelp reviews of all the restaurants in Vegas.\n\nWe called for reservations for 10:45am and were admitted at 11:08am. We arrived at noon to find a place to sit - which was a problem! The inside was a bit of a mess - tables for about 5 people in total. There's no seating for children and there are no TVs. The tables are set in front of the kitchen as you would expect. \n\nWe ordered the Chicken and Waffle Sandwich which comes with a side salad and bacon. Both options were yummy. The chicken on its own is a little salty and the egg in the sandwich is a little over cooked, and they're not very generous with the egg. My friend also ordered the waffle sandwich which came with fries. Overall, this was a great place to give a place to call home. Our waiter recommended the French Onion Soup which is basically a bagel with a nice piece of sour cream. We opted for both and both were very good. We decided to share the salad which comes with coleslaw, fried potatoes, and the fried green tomato. The salad was pretty good as well. I would have loved to sample an earlier version of the dish - it was a great find and one I was hoping to try again. The Greens were great too. \n\nWe'd highly recomend this place, but if you're a little hesitant and just want to try it, definitely go and see for yourself. I'm still keeping my fingers crossed that maybe they have a way to make the interior more fun\/attractive. I would recommend it if you're coming in at lunch time.<|endoftext|>
